Incorrect

void (() => {})();
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ void operator shouldn't be used on void; it should convey that a return value is being ignored

function foo() {}
void foo();
~~~~~~~~~~ void operator shouldn't be used on void; it should convey that a return value is being ignored

Correct

(() => {})();

function foo() {}
foo(); // nothing to discard

void Promise.resolve(); // intentionally ignore a Promise
